<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<CONTENT id="_3793148_1"><TITLE value="Session 8"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-46884693_1" alt="" width="489" height="340" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Introduction&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div&gt;During this session we will be investigating the frameworks used to help organisations protect against cyber attacks.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;News&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;More bad news about the Cyber security professionals - looks like original report was from the UK, but reflects Australian concerns.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/content/ia/article/2024/cyber-specialists-moonlighting-as-dark-web-criminals.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM20892" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Cyber specialists moonlighting as dark web criminals | Information Age | ACS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This next story is an update of the Microsoft Attack story from Session 3&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/content/ia/article/2024/hackers-lurk-in-microsoft-systems-for-3-months.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM20892" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hackers lurk in Microsoft systems for 3 months | Information Age | ACS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-03-20/notre-dame-uni-students-says-cyber-attack-playing-havoc/105075278" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Notre Dame uni students say outage creating enrolment, graduation, assignment mayhem - ABC News&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;(not News, but a look at verious Cyber Tools) &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.hirensbootcd.org/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Download | Hiren's BootCD PE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Topic&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This session you will e&lt;span style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;xamine methods used to protect an organisation’s data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;The main focus will be on the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;MITRE adversarial tactics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Techniques and Common Knowledge (ATT&amp;amp;CK)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;MITRE ATT&amp;amp;CK (&lt;strong&gt;Adversarial Tactics, Techniques and Common Knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;) is a framework, set of data matrices, and assessment tool developed by MITRE Corporation to help organizations understand their security readiness and uncover vulnerabilities in their defenses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of Session Activity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;Review the Lockheed Martin Cyber Kill Chain and the Mitre ATT&amp;amp;CK framework.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Consider how they are related.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Importantly, the Cyber Kill Chain has a military origin with external threats.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Portfolio Tasks&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check assessments tab.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Complete outstanding work&lt;/div&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
